(CLEARING THROAT)

1068
01:23:05,027 --> 01:23:06,904
(READING INDISTINCTLY)

1069
01:23:08,130 --> 01:23:10,041
That's very decent of him.

1070
01:23:10,099 --> 01:23:13,444
As Prime Minister, 
he always had good instincts.

1071
01:23:14,170 --> 01:23:15,649
-But that doesn't mean I know him. 
-But the...

1072
01:23:15,705 --> 01:23:18,743
That. That was taken at a reception 
in London

1073
01:23:19,175 --> 01:23:21,815
to mark the 10-year anniversary 
of the Arcadia.

1074
01:23:21,878 --> 01:23:24,324
-Arcadia? 
-Yeah, it's a little organization that I ran.

1075
01:23:24,380 --> 01:23:27,156
Very highbrow. 
No reason why you should have heard of it.

1076
01:23:27,216 --> 01:23:30,322
The Prime Minister graced us 
with his presence.

1077
01:23:30,486 --> 01:23:34,059
What can you remember of him 
from Cambridge?

1078
01:23:35,491 --> 01:23:38,335
-I'm sorry, you don't mind, do you? 
-No, not at all. Go ahead.

1079
01:23:38,394 --> 01:23:40,897
