1095
01:24:28,878 --> 01:24:30,585
My children would be mortified.

1096
01:24:30,646 --> 01:24:33,183
They're so much more puritanical 
than we were.

1097
01:24:33,249 --> 01:24:37,095
-Can you tell me about any of the others? 
-No, I'm afraid not.

1098
01:24:37,420 --> 01:24:40,594
The whole summer is a blur, 
a very happy blur.

1099
01:24:42,358 --> 01:24:45,703
Now, you were going to tell me 
about these pictures.

1100
01:24:46,362 --> 01:24:48,603
I got them from Michael McAra.

1101
01:24:49,465 --> 01:24:52,071
And he is whom, exactly?

1102
01:24:52,134 --> 01:24:54,614
My predecessor on Lang's memoirs.

1103
01:24:55,404 --> 01:24:57,975
-He resigned? 
-No, he died.

1104
01:24:58,875 --> 01:25:00,286
I'm sorry to hear that.

1105
01:25:00,343 --> 01:25:03,984
Yes, a couple of weeks ago. 
He drove up here to see you.

1106
01:25:04,313 --> 01:25:05,951
And he died a few hours afterwards.

1107
01:25:06,015 --> 01:25:09,485
He drove up to see me? 
No, I'm afraid you're mistaken.

1108
01:25:10,219 --> 01:25:13,257
-How did he die? 
-He drowned.

1109
01:25:13,322 --> 01:25:14,733
Poor fellow.

1110
01:25:15,858 --> 01:25:20,637
I've never really believed the myth that 
death by drowning is painless, have you?

1111
01:25:20,696 --> 01:25:23,199
