01:38:39,661 --> 01:38:41,368
I've been worried sick.

1212
01:38:41,430 --> 01:38:44,843
The police called to say 
they'd found the car on the ferry. Again!

1213
01:38:44,899 --> 01:38:49,211
I'm so sorry. I parked it, 
and then, and then I got off the boat.

1214
01:38:49,271 --> 01:38:52,252
What the hell were you doing 
on the mainland, anyway?

1215
01:38:52,307 --> 01:38:54,947
-l drove to New York. 
-Why?

1216
01:38:56,178 --> 01:38:58,317
I needed to see John Maddox.

1217
01:38:58,546 --> 01:39:00,219
And where are you now?

1218
01:39:00,281 --> 01:39:04,024
I'm still at the ferry terminal. 
I missed the last crossing.

1219
01:39:04,319 --> 01:39:06,390
You really are bloody hopeless!

1220
01:39:06,454 --> 01:39:09,765
I just had Adam on the phone, 
trying to get hold of you.

1221
01:39:09,825 --> 01:39:13,432
He's flying back tonight. 
He sounds in a right state.

1222
01:39:14,262 --> 01:39:15,969
You didn't tell him about us, did you?

1223
01:39:16,031 --> 01:39:17,101
God's sake, Ruth!

1224
01:39:17,165 --> 01:39:18,303
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

1225
01:39:18,500 --> 01:39:21,003
I've got to go. I'll call you back.

1226
01:39:27,042 --> 01:39:29,420
-Who is it? 
-Mr. Rycart sent me.

1227
01:39:30,378 --> 01:39:31,584
Hold on.

1228
01:40:01,442 --> 01:40:04,082
Just gonna do a quick check, 
if you don't mind.

1229
01:40:18,226 --> 01:40:20,399
Get your stuff together. We're leaving.

1230
01:40:24,532 --> 01:40:26,443
Hey! That's private!

1231
01:40:49,324 --> 01:40:51,429
-He's clean. 
-RICHARD: Thanks, Frank.

1232
01:40:55,763 --> 01:40:58,744
Sorry about that. Please, get in.

1233
01:41:14,716 --> 01:41:17,890
-You thought it was a trap? 
-It crossed my mind.

1234
01:41:17,952 --> 01:41:19,192
You do work for Lang.

1235
01:41:19,254 --> 01:41:21,256
Yeah, for three days. I hardly know the guy.

1236
01:41:21,322 --> 01:41:26,135
Who does? I worked for him for 15 years, 
till he fired me, and I still can't fathom him.

1237
01:41:26,194 --> 01:41:28,105
Yeah, his wife said more or less the same.

1238
01:41:28,162 --> 01:41:32,770
There you go. If someone as sharp as Ruth 
can't get him, what hope do we have?

1239
01:41:32,834 --> 01:41:35,440
-Tough day? 
-Yeah, you could say that.

1240
01:41:35,837 --> 01:41:37,407
You have the book?

1241
01:41:38,273 --> 01:41:39,377
FRANK: Yeah.

1242
01:41:39,874 --> 01:41:41,285
He's got it.

1243
01:41:48,483 --> 01:41:52,829
Before we go any further, I wonder 
if I might take a look at that book.

1244
01:41:57,358 --> 01:42:01,932
No. Before we go any further, 
there's a few things I'd like to know first.

1245
01:42:01,996 --> 01:42:04,909
Such as, 
why did Mike McAra have your number?

1246
01:42:09,538 --> 01:42:10,915
Okay. Sure.

1247
01:42:11,706 --> 01:42:13,185
He was helping me.

1248
01:42:14,075 --> 01:42:15,213
Mc Ara? How?

1249
01:42:15,276 --> 01:42:18,849
Mike found the documents linking Lang 
to the torture flights.

1250
01:42:18,914 --> 01:42:20,552
What? It was McAra 
who gave you the documents?

1251
01:42:20,615 --> 01:42:24,893
-Yeah, Mike McAra. The loyalest of the loyal. 
-But why?

1252
01:42:24,952 --> 01:42:28,525
He didn't like discovering 
he was working for a war criminal.

1253
01:42:28,590 --> 01:42:29,898
Would you?

1254
01:42:30,825 --> 01:42:32,702
Oh, I forgot. You are.

1255
01:42:34,996 --> 01:42:36,236
The book?

1256
01:43:05,960 --> 01:43:07,439
Well, don't tell me 
you're gonna read it now.

1257
01:43:07,495 --> 01:43:09,907
Not all of it. Just the beginning.

1258
01:43:10,532 --> 01:43:12,671
There's something very important about it.

1259
01:43:12,734 --> 01:43:15,271
Yeah. it's the cure for insomnia.

1260
01:43:15,336 --> 01:43:18,442
There you go, guys. 
Can I get you anything else?

1261
01:43:18,506 --> 01:43:20,110
No, thanks, love.

1262
01:43:24,179 --> 01:43:28,719
Mike said he'd discovered something new. 
it's the last time he called me.

1263
01:43:29,083 --> 01:43:32,553
He said it explained everything that had 
gone wrong when we were in government.

1264
01:43:32,620 --> 01:43:35,328
-What was it? 
-He wouldn't say over the phone.

1265
01:43:35,390 --> 01:43:40,237
He just kept saying if anything happened 
to him, the truth was in Lang's memoirs.

1266
01:43:40,595 --> 01:43:42,268
"it's all there in the beginning."

1267
01:43:42,330 --> 01:43:43,866
The beginning?

1268
01:43:44,966 --> 01:43:46,946
Then he means Cambridge.

1269
01:43:58,813 --> 01:44:00,121
What the hell's this?

1270
01:44:00,181 --> 01:44:02,991
That is Lang, and that is Paul Emmett.

1271
01:44:03,351 --> 01:44:06,355
Emmett? The Arcadia guy. So what?

1272
01:44:06,421 --> 01:44:10,096
On the day that Mike McAra died, 
he drove up to see Emmett,

1273
01:44:10,525 --> 01:44:12,436
and I think he was murdered 
on his way home.

1274
01:44:12,494 --> 01:44:13,871
-What? 
-l went to see Emmett today,

1275
01:44:13,928 --> 01:44:17,171
and two guys followed me from his house. 
That's why I called you.

1276
01:44:18,400 --> 01:44:20,880
At the time that this photograph was taken,

1277
01:44:21,436 --> 01:44:25,384
Paul Emmett was an officer in the CIA.

1278
01:44:25,873 --> 01:44:26,908
Emmett?

1279
01:44:26,975 --> 01:44:29,956
-Foreign Resources Division. 
-Oh, my God.

1280
01:44:31,579 --> 01:44:34,287
You realize how important this is, 
don't you?

1281
01:44:34,716 --> 01:44:37,595
This explains why Lang went into politics.

1282
01:44:38,086 --> 01:44:41,898
Everyone knows he didn't have 
a political thought in his pretty little head.

1283
01:44:42,456 --> 01:44:47,166
This is why he rose so quickly, 
with a little help from his friends.

1284
01:44:47,762 --> 01:44:50,003
-Well, do you think it's possible... 
-Okay, a quiz for you.

1285
01:44:50,065 --> 01:44:53,512
Name one decision Lang made in 10 years 
as Prime Minister

1286
01:44:53,568 --> 01:44:56,344
which wasn't in the interests of the USA.

1287
01:44:58,039 --> 01:45:00,849
Well, come on, it's not a trick question.

1288
01:45:01,409 --> 01:45:05,084
Iraq, Middle East policy, Star Wars defense,

1289
01:45:05,980 --> 01:45:09,484
buying American nuclear missiles, 
support of terrorist rendition.

1290
01:45:09,550 --> 01:45:13,191
The sacking of any minister 
Washington didn't like,

1291
01:45:13,721 --> 01:45:15,564
including yours truly.

1292
01:45:16,157 --> 01:45:17,761
McAra was right.

1293
01:45:18,259 --> 01:45:19,704
This explains everything.

1294
01:45:19,761 --> 01:45:21,001
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

1295
01:45:24,532 --> 01:45:26,136
it's Amelia Bly.

1296
01:45:26,634 --> 01:45:27,977
Answer it.

1297
01:45:30,071 --> 01:45:33,416
-Hello, Amelia. 
-Good evening. I have Adam for you.

1298
01:45:34,742 --> 01:45:35,914
(SOFTLY) Lang.

1299
01:45:36,244 --> 01:45:37,848
ADAM: We're coming to get you.

1300
01:45:37,912 --> 01:45:39,050
What?

1301
01:45:39,480 --> 01:45:41,892
Ruth tells me 
you're stuck at the ferry terminal.

1302
01:45:41,949 --> 01:45:44,054
We've just taken off from New York.

1303
01:45:44,118 --> 01:45:46,928
Pilot says we can stop by and pick you up.

1304
01:45:47,522 --> 01:45:49,729
Really? There's no need.

1305
01:45:49,791 --> 01:45:52,032
We've got a book to write, remember?

1306
01:45:53,695 --> 01:45:55,333
Hold on a sec, Adam.

1307
01:45:57,365 --> 01:46:00,107
(SOFTLY) He said he wants to 
pick me up in his private jet.

1308
01:46:00,168 --> 01:46:02,079
-Say yes. 
-What if it's a trap?

1309
01:46:02,136 --> 01:46:05,379
If you refuse, he'll get suspicious. 
Tell him yes.

1310
01:46:07,742 --> 01:46:11,713
That'd be great, Adam. Yeah, thanks. 
I'll get to the airport.

1311
01:46:12,246 --> 01:46:13,725
See you there.

1312
01:46:15,750 --> 01:46:17,423
He sounds worried.

1313
01:46:18,887 --> 01:46:20,457
I really don't think this is a good idea.

1314
01:46:20,521 --> 01:46:21,727
You have no choice.

1315
01:46:21,789 --> 01:46:23,826
Emmett must have told Lang 
that I'd been to see him.

1316
01:46:23,891 --> 01:46:26,269
So, what's he gonna do about it? 
Dump you in the ocean?

1317
01:46:26,327 --> 01:46:29,137
-Well, it happened before! 
-Which means it can't happen again.

1318
01:46:29,197 --> 01:46:33,407
He can't drown two ghostwriters, 
for God's sake. You're not kittens.

1319
01:46:36,037 --> 01:46:38,643
All this is just theory. 
We don't have any proof.

1320
01:46:38,706 --> 01:46:40,913
-You'll get us the proof. 
-Me?

1321
01:46:40,975 --> 01:46:43,512
You're his ghostwriter. 
Presumably, he lets you tape him.

1322
01:46:43,578 --> 01:46:45,819
-l use discs, actually. 
-Discs, tapes.

1323
01:46:45,880 --> 01:46:48,190
You've got to confront him with this. 
Record his reaction.

1324
01:46:48,249 --> 01:46:49,990
Even if he denies it, it's something.

1325
01:46:50,051 --> 01:46:54,193
I'm in a tricky position here. 
I signed a confidentiality agreement.

1326
01:46:54,255 --> 01:46:55,325
It's a bit late for that.

1327
01:46:55,389 --> 01:46:58,666
-it means the discs are his property. 
-The court can subpoena them.

1328
01:46:59,427 --> 01:47:02,033
And what if I don't record any discs?

1329
01:47:02,097 --> 01:47:04,737
Then you'll be subpoenaed 
and forced to repeat this whole story.

1330
01:47:04,799 --> 01:47:05,903
Then I'll deny it.

1331
01:47:05,966 --> 01:47:07,968
Then I'll give them this.

1332
01:47:10,572 --> 01:47:12,711
Frank is recording every word.

1333
01:47:12,774 --> 01:47:14,412
Aren't you, Frank?

1334
01:47:17,979 --> 01:47:19,481
Oh! Come on!

1335
01:47:19,547 --> 01:47:21,390
Don't look so shocked. 
What did you expect?

1336
01:47:21,449 --> 01:47:23,861
That I'd come into a meeting 
with a man working for Lang

1337
01:47:23,918 --> 01:47:26,125
without taking any precautions?

1338
01:47:26,754 --> 01:47:29,496
Except you're not working 
for Lang anymore.

1339
01:47:29,557 --> 01:47:31,468
You're working for the good guys.

1340
01:47:33,194 --> 01:47:35,367
You know all this is pointless, don't you?

1341
01:47:35,896 --> 01:47:39,139
In the end, he'll just retire over here 
with his CIA pension,

1342
01:47:39,200 --> 01:47:42,875
and he'll tell you and the bloody 
war crimes court to go and fuck yourselves.

1343
01:47:56,517 --> 01:47:59,691
Good evening, sir. 
Hatherton welcomes you aboard.

1344
01:48:00,121 --> 01:48:01,429
Thank you.

1345
01:48:02,857 --> 01:48:04,734
It's my first time in a private jet.

1346
01:48:04,792 --> 01:48:06,669
Well, let's hope it's not your last.

1347
01:48:18,706 --> 01:48:19,946
Hi, man.

1348
01:48:21,142 --> 01:48:23,122
-Take your seat. 
-Thanks.

1349
01:48:24,512 --> 01:48:28,016
-Hey, bring my ghost a Calvados. 
-Yes, sir.

1350
01:48:49,304 --> 01:48:50,510
Do you mind?

1351
01:48:50,572 --> 01:48:52,381
Leave it off for now.

1352
01:48:52,940 --> 01:48:55,887
Ruth said you were in New York 
to see Maddox.

1353
01:48:57,312 --> 01:48:59,189
-That's right. 
-How was he?

1354
01:49:00,047 --> 01:49:01,117
He was fine.

1355
01:49:01,182 --> 01:49:02,684
Full of energy?

1356
01:49:02,983 --> 01:49:05,486
-You know John. 
-Yes, I do know John.

1357
01:49:06,887 --> 01:49:09,629
As a matter of fact, I was just with him.

1358
01:49:09,691 --> 01:49:12,103
You never saw him today, did you?

1359
01:49:13,995 --> 01:49:15,065
No.

1360
01:49:15,730 --> 01:49:17,607
Do you have something to tell me?

1361
01:49:17,665 --> 01:49:19,440
I went to see Emmett.

1362
01:49:19,534 --> 01:49:22,811
(LAUGHING) That windbag! Why?

1363
01:49:22,870 --> 01:49:24,315
I know about you and Emmett.

1364
01:49:24,371 --> 01:49:26,351
-Me and Emmett? 
-l know that he was your...

1365
01:49:26,407 --> 01:49:29,115
-My?
-...handler, if that's what they're called.

1366
01:49:29,176 --> 01:49:32,817
-My handler? 
-Yeah, that he was your handler in the CIA.

1367
01:49:33,447 --> 01:49:34,517
(COUGHING)

1368
01:49:36,450 --> 01:49:37,520
(LAUGHING)

1369
01:49:43,724 --> 01:49:45,863
Oh, my God.

1370
01:49:47,895 --> 01:49:50,000
You're serious, aren't you?

1371
01:49:58,373 --> 01:50:02,082
When McAra found this, 
he went to Boston to show it to Emmett,

1372
01:50:02,143 --> 01:50:05,716
and he died on the way home, 
and I think he was murdered.

1373
01:50:06,280 --> 01:50:09,090
I think you've had a few too many 
of those already.

1374
01:50:09,150 --> 01:50:13,394
It was McAra who believed that Emmett told 
you to go into politics in the first place.

1375
01:50:13,454 --> 01:50:15,593
-Emmett? I barely knew the man. 
-And that story of yours

1376
01:50:15,656 --> 01:50:19,502
about why you joined the party and Ruth 
and the canvassing, well, the dates don't fit.

1377
01:50:19,560 --> 01:50:21,403
I got the dates wrong. Big deal!

1378
01:50:21,462 --> 01:50:22,941
Then when he found this photograph,

1379
01:50:22,997 --> 01:50:25,136
and he heard the rumors 
about Emmett being in the CIA...

1380
01:50:25,199 --> 01:50:27,008
-Rumors? 
-It's on the Internet.

1381
01:50:27,068 --> 01:50:30,379
I've never heard such utter balls 
in my entire life.

1382
01:50:31,939 --> 01:50:36,945
Mike would never have believed such crap. 
He was too clever. Too loyal.

1383
01:50:37,612 --> 01:50:39,751
Mike betrayed you to Rycart.

1384
01:50:44,018 --> 01:50:46,259
-How do you know that? 
-He told me.

1385
01:50:47,188 --> 01:50:48,360
Rycart?

1386
01:50:50,358 --> 01:50:51,701
He's lying.

1387
01:50:56,464 --> 01:50:59,911
This phone number on the back 
of the photograph, it's Rycart's.

1388
01:51:00,534 --> 01:51:03,743
The handwriting, that's McAra's.

1389
01:51:04,438 --> 01:51:05,542
Mike.

1390
01:51:07,508 --> 01:51:10,148
-Mike, Mike. 
-And you knew he was disillusioned.

1391
01:51:10,211 --> 01:51:11,849
You had a big row with him 
just before he died.

1392
01:51:11,913 --> 01:51:15,952
Yes, I know, but he never mentioned this. 
This is just... This is grotesque.

1393
01:51:17,051 --> 01:51:19,190
I've never taken orders from anyone.

1394
01:51:19,253 --> 01:51:22,325
Whatever I did, 
I did because I believed it was right.

1395
01:51:22,390 --> 01:51:24,996
What, even supporting illegal kidnapping 
for torture?

1396
01:51:25,059 --> 01:51:29,030
Oh, for God's sake, 
spare me the bleeding-heart bullshit!

1397
01:51:29,096 --> 01:51:31,098
Do you know what I'd do 
if I was in power again?

1398
01:51:31,165 --> 01:51:33,270
I'd have two queues at airports.

1399
01:51:33,334 --> 01:51:36,315
One for flights 
where we'd done no background checks,

1400
01:51:36,370 --> 01:51:41,251
infringed on no one's civil bloody liberties, 
used no intelligence gained by torture.

1401
01:51:41,309 --> 01:51:44,813
And on the other flight, 
we'd do everything we possibly could

1402
01:51:44,878 --> 01:51:46,585
to make it perfectly safe.

1403
01:51:46,647 --> 01:51:49,457
And then we'd see which plane 
the Rycarts of this world

1404
01:51:49,517 --> 01:51:51,292
would put their bloody kids on!

1405
01:51:51,352 --> 01:51:53,161
(SHOUTING) 
And you can put that in the book!

1406
01:52:17,645 --> 01:52:19,147
(PROTESTERS CLAMORING)

1407
01:52:19,781 --> 01:52:21,021
MAN: Go home!

1408
01:52:21,516 --> 01:52:23,052
WOMAN: Go home!

1409
01:52:24,285 --> 01:52:26,162
MAN: Here comes the killer!

1410
01:52:26,220 --> 01:52:29,030
WOMAN: Prosecute for torture!

1411
01:52:29,090 --> 01:52:30,569
FEMALE REPORTER: Over here, Mr. Lang!

1412
01:52:30,624 --> 01:52:33,935
Mr. Lang! 
Mr. Lang, will you live in America?

1413
01:52:33,994 --> 01:52:35,371
(PROTESTERS CLAMORING)

1414
01:52:36,464 --> 01:52:38,967
Mr. Lang, will you take 
American citizenship?

1415
01:52:39,033 --> 01:52:40,205
(PROTESTERS BOOING)

1416
01:52:43,671 --> 01:52:46,584
When we get back to the house, 
we need to have a meeting.

1417
01:52:47,308 --> 01:52:48,412
(GUNSHOT)

1418
01:52:49,577 --> 01:52:51,488
-RUTH: Oh, my God! 
-Murderer!

1419
01:52:51,545 --> 01:52:53,024
BODYGUARD: Firing from the roof!

1420
01:52:54,382 --> 01:52:55,622
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

1421
01:52:58,185 --> 01:53:02,224
RUTH: Let me goto him! No! No!

1422
01:53:05,459 --> 01:53:07,097
Move, move, move!

1423
01:53:15,803 --> 01:53:17,282
(POLICE RADIO CHATTER)

1424
01:53:47,301 --> 01:53:49,144
FBI AGENT 1: 
How long had you known Mr. Lang?

1425
01:53:49,203 --> 01:53:51,740
-Couple of days. 
-In what capacity?

1426
01:53:51,805 --> 01:53:53,512
I was his ghost.

1427
01:53:53,574 --> 01:53:55,178
His ghostwriter.

1428
01:53:57,011 --> 01:53:58,786
Do you recognize this man?

1429
01:54:00,448 --> 01:54:04,419
He was one of the protesters. 
His son was killed in Iraq.

1430
01:54:04,485 --> 01:54:06,431
Did you ever speak with him?

1431
01:54:06,487 --> 01:54:09,024
He was in the bar one night 
in the hotel where I was staying.

1432
01:54:09,090 --> 01:54:10,831
FBI AGENT 2: But did you speak with him?

1433
01:54:10,892 --> 01:54:13,065
He asked me if I knew where Adam Lang 
was staying on the island.

1434
01:54:13,127 --> 01:54:16,574
-l told him that I didn't. 
-Did you report this conversation?

1435
01:54:16,630 --> 01:54:17,665
Sorry?

1436
01:54:17,732 --> 01:54:20,269
Did you report this conversation 
to Mr. Lang's protection team?

1437
01:54:20,334 --> 01:54:21,369
No.

1438
01:54:21,702 --> 01:54:23,943
What was Mr. Lang's demeanor 
this evening?

1439
01:54:24,005 --> 01:54:27,248
He was... He was fine. He seemed fine.

1440
01:54:28,175 --> 01:54:31,281
One witness said she thought 
she heard Mr. Lang shouting at you.

1441
01:54:31,945 --> 01:54:33,015
No.

1442
01:55:00,808 --> 01:55:03,254
-We're gonna need your passport. 
-Why?

1443
01:55:03,310 --> 01:55:07,224
A serious crime was just committed 
in US territory, and you're the key witness.

1444
01:55:13,487 --> 01:55:15,228
We need to keep you close.

1445
01:55:20,194 --> 01:55:23,869
MALE REPORTER: Like a fallen soldier, 
